cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a new hybrid analog and digital combining architecture for millimeter wave (mmWave) multi-user multiple-input multiple-output (MU-MIMO) systems, which involves signal processing and information theory concepts. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The proposed structure aims to enhance the sum-rates and reduce power consumption in the RF circuit, which are important considerations in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia): The proposed structure is designed for millimeter wave (mmWave) multi-user multiple-input multiple-output (MU-MIMO) systems, which are commonly used in multimedia applications. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a new architecture for signal combining in the analog domain, which involves control and optimization of the phases of signals in the RF circuit. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The proposed structure involves the use of active/inactive switches and constant phase shifters (CPS) to control the phases of signals in the RF circuit, which are hardware components.
